    Ann Rheum Dis
    Concordance and discordance in SLE clinical trial outcome measures: analysis of three anifrolumab phase 2/3 trials.
Across trials, most patients had concordant BICLA/SRI(4) outcomes and dual BICLA/SRI(4) responses favoured anifrolumab. A BICLA non-responder/SRI(4) responder subgroup was identified where imbalances of key factors driving the BICLA/SRI(4) discordance (disease activity, glucocorticoid taper) disproportionately favoured the TULIP-1 placebo group. Careful attention to baseline disease activity and monitoring glucocorticoid taper variation will be essential in future SLE trials. Trail registration numbers NCT02446912 and NCT02446899.
